<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER - REMOVE - MAIN CASE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>MAIN CASE</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302341">Figure 41</hotlnk>,
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302342">Figure 42</hotlnk>
            and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302343">Figure 43</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1302341" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302341" filename="../figg13/G1302341.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 41. Main Case &#38; Shift Forks - Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1302342" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302342" filename="../figg13/G1302342.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 42. Clutch Housing - Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1302343" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302343" filename="../figg13/G1302343.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 43. Main Case Gears - Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the case bolts. Use pry bars in the milled slots to help separate the case from the
                clutch housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302344">Figure 44</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302344" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302344" filename="../figg13/G1302344.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 44. Remove Case Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the auxiliary countershaft front bearings are damaged, remove and replace them (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302345">Figure 45</hotlnk>). Also remove the rear countershaft bearing cup races
                before removing the main case. This will prevent them from falling into the transmission.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302345" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302345" filename="../figg13/G1302345.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 45. Remove Countershaft Front Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift the case from the clutch housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302346">Figure 46</hotlnk>). Note that the rear shift bar support bracket remains with
                the case.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302346" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302346" filename="../figg13/G1302346.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 46. Lift Case From Clutch Housing</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>When moving heavy parts, use a chain hoist to help prevent personal injury.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
